<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id90678c19-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s4071e"><num value="4071e">§ 4071e.</num><heading> Deductions and withholdings from pay</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id90678c1a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s4071e/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Basic pay</heading><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id90678c1b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s4071e/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The employing agency shall deduct and withhold from the basic pay of each participant the applicable percentage of basic pay specified in paragraph (2) of this subsection minus the percentage then in effect under <ref href="/us/usc/t26/s3101/a">section 3101(a) of title 26</ref> (relating to the rate of tax for old age, survivors, and disability insurance).</content>
</paragraph>
